WEBVTT

00:08.634 --> 00:09.669
[SNIFFS]

00:09.843 --> 00:11.629
Mm. Spicy.

00:12.095 --> 00:14.711
Who's a pretty girl? You're a pretty girl.

00:14.890 --> 00:17.723
You're pretty. Yes, you are. Grrr!

00:17.893 --> 00:19.429
Piss off.

00:20.562 --> 00:23.429
I know it's not too good
to be all matchy-matchy...

00:23.607 --> 00:29.443
...but you and your dusky little bloodbeast
are totally at odds with my decor.

00:29.613 --> 00:33.401
Well, nobody cares what you
think about anything. Shut up.

00:36.286 --> 00:38.663
-l'm awful sorry.
-No, you're not.

00:38.830 --> 00:40.115
Oh, good girl.

00:40.290 --> 00:43.953
-Just ignore him. He's the cleaning lady.
-Psycho fugly thug.

00:44.753 --> 00:45.788
[GROWLS]

00:45.963 --> 00:48.295
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

00:54.096 --> 00:55.632
Bill?

02:29.232 --> 02:33.066
-You know him?
-I thought I did.

02:33.236 --> 02:35.898
-Why is she here?
-Why is she here?

02:36.073 --> 02:38.564
-She wants to be with me.
-Hence the restraints.

02:38.742 --> 02:41.984
-She's mine.
-Relax. Nobody wants her.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.618
Certainly not I.

02:45.332 --> 02:48.916
-Why is he here?
-Because I have a present for you, sir.

02:49.461 --> 02:50.917
Please.

02:52.130 --> 02:56.715
-You're not supposed to bring work home.
-Darling, king.

02:57.344 --> 03:02.839
Franklin, you never disappoint.
Shall we retire to the study?

03:05.769 --> 03:09.353
What is going on here?
What's wrong with you?

03:09.523 --> 03:14.608
Yes, Bill.
Your behavior is somewhat erratic.

03:15.237 --> 03:17.398
Help me.

03:19.366 --> 03:20.822
No.

03:38.635 --> 03:41.627
As always,
the deposit will go to your trust account.

03:41.805 --> 03:43.636
But I want cash.

03:44.433 --> 03:46.048
Last time you had any real money...

03:46.226 --> 03:49.935
...you ended up at the slots in Biloxi,
slaughtering a group of elderly women.

03:50.105 --> 03:54.144
-They wouldn't let me have a turn.
-Why are you dragging another girl around?

03:54.317 --> 03:55.306
[SIGHS]

03:55.485 --> 03:57.396
So sloppy.

03:58.405 --> 04:00.896
I'm tired of cleaning up after you.

04:01.074 --> 04:04.783
-This is one is spectacularly different.
-Hm.

04:04.953 --> 04:07.740
She's such a fucking disaster.
We could be twins.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.291
The attraction is electric.

04:10.459 --> 04:14.577
Franklin, you're a huge freak.

04:15.172 --> 04:16.503
But I like your work.

04:18.842 --> 04:23.586
-Bill Compton is lying to me.
-Yes, sir.

04:24.055 --> 04:27.639
Who keeps a dossier on his human?
Why would he care about her family tree?

04:27.809 --> 04:31.427
Sophie Anne's overstated perfume
is all over this.

04:31.605 --> 04:32.936
That's what I thought.

04:34.191 --> 04:37.854
She's already escaped us once,
this barmaid.

04:38.028 --> 04:39.859
Send a wolf, what'd you expect?

04:42.616 --> 04:47.485
Maybe I should send you back to
Bon Temps to acquire Sookie Stackhouse.

04:47.662 --> 04:49.527
I don't have to go anywhere.

04:50.373 --> 04:52.659
She's in Jackson.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.797
[LAUGHS]

04:58.840 --> 05:02.128
I'll let you play your little game
of hard to get.

05:02.511 --> 05:05.969
You're gonna be that much sweeter
when you're mine again.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.596
You know, Russell was right.

05:09.726 --> 05:12.183
You're not very smart.

05:12.354 --> 05:16.563
You played yourself into a corner,
you tiresome cow.

05:22.280 --> 05:25.397
What happened back there?
Why were they all shifting?

05:25.575 --> 05:27.406
-You almost shifted.
-Couldn't help it.

05:27.577 --> 05:30.034
When that energy starts rolling,
it takes you over.

05:30.205 --> 05:35.416
We're lucky we got out of there alive.
Fuck! Ugh!

05:35.585 --> 05:37.962
-I know it was terrible--
-You don't know anything.

05:38.129 --> 05:40.211
If you don't slow down,
you're gonna kill us.

05:40.382 --> 05:44.421
And I am not gonna die because of your
shitty girlfriend and a Mississippi pothole!

05:46.096 --> 05:47.711
[TIRES SCREECHING]

05:52.727 --> 05:55.104
I had to be mean to make you listen.

05:55.730 --> 05:58.767
-l'm sorry.
-She wasn't always shitty.

05:59.192 --> 06:00.648
We were great together.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.990
When she wasn't drinking or cheating.

06:06.575 --> 06:09.191
She used to play horseshoes
with my dad...

06:09.369 --> 06:10.950
...help my mom plant tomatoes.

06:11.121 --> 06:14.033
But tonight she was half-naked
in a wolf skin, getting branded.

06:16.084 --> 06:19.576
-Tell me more about Russell Edgington.
-He's just some rich vampire.

06:19.754 --> 06:22.666
-That's all I knew till tonight.
-I gotta talk to him.

06:22.841 --> 06:26.459
-Are you out of your fucking mind?
-The brand, the blood, the vampire.

06:26.636 --> 06:29.252
He knows where Bill is,
or he knows who knows.

06:29.431 --> 06:32.298
I promised Eric
I'd keep you out of trouble.

06:32.934 --> 06:34.970
You ain't going near him, Sookie.

06:43.320 --> 06:47.734
ERIC: This is completely unnecessary.
I told you I come in peace.

06:48.325 --> 06:51.317
Hello. Have we met?

06:51.494 --> 06:54.736
Eric Northman, sheriff, Louisiana Area 5.

06:54.915 --> 06:56.496
I've come to see the king.

06:57.417 --> 07:01.001
Talbot, royal consort.

07:01.171 --> 07:03.002
Permit me to facilitate.

07:04.674 --> 07:06.585
Russell!

07:07.010 --> 07:08.966
Let him go, you idiots.

07:09.387 --> 07:10.593
Thank you.

07:14.351 --> 07:16.808
l humbly request permission
to hunt your territory...

07:16.978 --> 07:18.843
...for the vampire missing from my area.

07:19.314 --> 07:22.852
I appreciate your courtesy, Eric.
It's very old-world.

07:23.318 --> 07:26.685
Nobody has manners anymore.
It was all so beautiful once.

07:27.197 --> 07:30.689
-Your fugitive, what's his name again?
-Bill Compton.

07:31.159 --> 07:34.651
l'm responsible for him,
and I'm ashamed to admit it...

07:34.829 --> 07:36.865
...but he's wanted
for selling vampire blood.

07:37.040 --> 07:38.701
Oh, no, no.

07:39.751 --> 07:43.335
-That's heinous. Are you sure?
ERIC: Hm.

07:43.713 --> 07:45.214
Let's ask him.

07:45.757 --> 07:46.997
Voila.

07:47.175 --> 07:50.667
He's not missing,
and he's way too square to deal V.

07:53.056 --> 07:55.638
You tried to pin that on me?

07:56.059 --> 07:58.425
We all know it's your queen behind this,
Northman.

07:58.603 --> 08:00.719
And that you did the selling for her.

08:00.897 --> 08:04.060
You see, Mr. Compton has accepted
a position in my court...

08:04.234 --> 08:07.897
...and therefore keeps nothing from me.

08:09.948 --> 08:13.657
Oh. You're here of your own accord.

08:14.953 --> 08:17.160
Which means....

08:17.330 --> 08:19.742
Sookie is no longer mine.

08:21.584 --> 08:22.664
Ah.

08:22.836 --> 08:25.748
A king in front of them,
a queen behind them...

08:25.922 --> 08:28.709
...and they're talking about a human girl.

08:28.883 --> 08:29.872
Men.

08:30.051 --> 08:31.757
[RUSSELL CHUCKLING]

08:31.928 --> 08:35.512
Your Majesty, I confess.

08:37.308 --> 08:40.721
I sold the blood at my queen's command
and accused Bill to protect her.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.436
So, what do I do now?

08:44.858 --> 08:47.691
Unless I give the Magister Compton,
he'll murder my progeny.

08:48.653 --> 08:51.269
Darling, so sad.

08:51.573 --> 08:53.154
[GROANS]

08:53.408 --> 08:59.404
The Magister is a nasty little
anachronistic toad...

08:59.581 --> 09:01.617
...a ridiculous remnant
of the Middle Ages.

09:01.791 --> 09:05.283
The only power he has over us
is the power we give him.

09:07.964 --> 09:11.456
There may be a way
to solve all our problems.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.126
Sleep here.

09:15.430 --> 09:17.295
You're more than welcome.

09:19.309 --> 09:20.389
How can I refuse?

09:35.867 --> 09:38.108
ALCIDE: You can'tjust walk back in here.
Give me my key.

09:38.286 --> 09:40.117
DEBBIE:
Shut up! Don't tell me what to do!

09:40.288 --> 09:42.495
It's my key,
and I'll use it whenever I want!

09:42.665 --> 09:44.496
ALCIDE:
You walked out on me. You got no right.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.749
DEBBIE: We'd still be together
if you weren't so weak!

09:46.920 --> 09:49.536
ALCIDE: Keep it down.
-Don't tell me to keep it down!

09:49.714 --> 09:51.921
Because I don't give a shit
about the neighbors!

09:52.425 --> 09:54.837
-I'm here to save your fucking life.
-Liar.

09:55.011 --> 09:58.094
You drug addict.
You sold your soul to a vamp. I saw you.

09:58.264 --> 10:02.633
He's more than a vamp.
Oh, you ignorant redneck.

10:02.811 --> 10:05.848
-If he knew what you saw--
-Fuck him.

10:06.231 --> 10:07.971
I'm warning you...

10:08.149 --> 10:11.858
...if anybody finds out
what went on at Lou Pine's--

10:14.989 --> 10:17.526
That's your neighbor?

10:18.201 --> 10:21.364
-Oh, hell, no.
-She got nothing to do with this.

10:21.538 --> 10:24.029
You're fucking my wolf, bitch.
In my house.

10:24.207 --> 10:26.493
DEBBIE: Like I did with Coot and Roy
and Bobby and Travis.

10:26.668 --> 10:29.705
Like you did with Coot and Roy
and Bobby and Travis.

10:29.879 --> 10:31.164
What'd you say to me, whore?

10:31.339 --> 10:33.876
I'm strong enough to throw you out,
blood or no blood.

10:34.050 --> 10:35.836
No, I'm not sleeping with him.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.467
But you traded this good person
who loves you...

10:38.638 --> 10:40.720
...for a shot of V,
that burn on your back...

10:40.890 --> 10:44.883
...and a dumb biker who's half the man
and half the wolf that Alcide is.

10:45.061 --> 10:47.347
I will fuck you up!

10:47.522 --> 10:48.728
I will cut you!

10:49.941 --> 10:51.556
Sookie, back off.

10:52.068 --> 10:55.560
Where is Bill Compton?

10:56.364 --> 10:59.231
DEBBIE:
Who the hell is Bill Compton?

11:11.838 --> 11:13.749
Do you like your new gown?

11:14.132 --> 11:16.748
Oh. Yes.

11:19.429 --> 11:22.296
I picked it out especially for my lover.

11:22.473 --> 11:24.805
Thank you so much.

11:25.476 --> 11:31.938
Even when I'm away from you,
I can feel your flesh molded to me.

11:32.108 --> 11:34.474
That's how close we are now.

11:34.652 --> 11:38.315
-That's really sweet.
-I know.

11:40.074 --> 11:42.065
Almost forgot.

11:43.203 --> 11:45.364
You have a text message.

11:45.788 --> 11:47.744
"Bitch, where are you?"

11:48.958 --> 11:51.574
You said no boyfriends. Who is he?
Who's Lafayette?

11:53.046 --> 11:54.536
I'll rip your throat out!

11:54.714 --> 11:56.045
[TARA GAGGING]

11:56.216 --> 11:58.878
He's my cousin.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.963
And he's-- And he's gay.

12:01.638 --> 12:02.969
[TARA COUGHING]

12:04.057 --> 12:07.641
Oh. Well, how do I get rid of him?

12:07.810 --> 12:09.391
How about, um....

12:10.605 --> 12:12.095
"I'm busy, bitch"?

12:12.649 --> 12:15.391
No, "bitch." He wrote "bitch."
Too many "bitches." "Hooker"?

12:15.568 --> 12:17.650
In his other messages,
he calls you "hooker."

12:17.820 --> 12:21.608
"Hooker." No, "hookah."
That's a water pipe. Heh, heh.

12:21.783 --> 12:24.650
Tell him I'm okay.

12:24.827 --> 12:27.819
Say, "Trust me, motherfucker."

12:28.915 --> 12:32.453
"Trust me, motherfucker." Brilliant.

12:32.627 --> 12:37.496
Hey, Tara, watch how fast
I type "motherfucker."

12:37.674 --> 12:39.164
[PHONE BEEPING]

12:39.342 --> 12:43.506
-It's cool, right?
-Yeah. Amazing.

12:43.680 --> 12:46.922
I'll delete it so you can watch again.

12:48.685 --> 12:50.346
[PHONE BEEPING]

12:50.520 --> 12:53.011
Look. Look at me.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.107
Love you.

13:00.029 --> 13:04.523
-I'm a fan of the regular mulch, myself.
-Oh. Oh.

13:04.701 --> 13:08.364
Oh, that's good for everyday,
but I love that red mulch. Yeah.

13:08.538 --> 13:12.451
I use it in all my flowerbeds. It would
look so good by your wishing well.

13:12.625 --> 13:15.867
I don't know. That seems kind of wild.

13:20.717 --> 13:22.548
Morning, Kenya.

13:22.719 --> 13:24.425
Morning, Kevin.

13:25.888 --> 13:29.051
-Morning.
-Morning.

13:29.475 --> 13:32.808
-What you doing here?
-What am I doing? I'm here to work.

13:34.314 --> 13:37.272
-Really?
-Mm-hm. Chomping at the bit.

13:37.442 --> 13:39.558
Point me at the crime scene
and let's get her.

13:39.736 --> 13:42.728
Acting Sheriff Andy Bellefleur,
would you come out here, please?

13:43.197 --> 13:46.030
ANDY: Can it wait?
I was just going to the restroom.

13:46.200 --> 13:48.987
Morning, boss. I'm ready for my first day.

13:57.754 --> 14:01.167
I guess this means
you find my performance inadequate.

14:01.341 --> 14:05.505
I will if you don't get out there to the
corner and cross them little kids to school.

14:06.971 --> 14:08.677
What's going on, Andy?

14:08.848 --> 14:11.931
Why does Jason Stackhouse
need a desk in the Sheriff's Department?

14:12.101 --> 14:13.966
ANDY: Nobody else is using it.
What do you care?

14:14.145 --> 14:17.888
Why don't you run those folders in the
conference room over to the courthouse?

14:19.567 --> 14:21.774
Please, Deputy Jones.

14:22.612 --> 14:24.193
[SCOFFS]

14:26.908 --> 14:28.114
I don't want a desk.

14:28.284 --> 14:32.368
I wanna be out in the field,
where it's real. That's where I shine.

14:32.538 --> 14:34.870
This ain't magic, Jason.
You gotta learn the ropes.

14:35.041 --> 14:37.578
Trust me,
I'm pushing you through fast as I can.

14:37.752 --> 14:44.544
Now, Rosie's home with female pains, so
for now, you're in charge of the phones.

14:44.967 --> 14:47.379
Can I at least have a uniform?

14:48.346 --> 14:50.553
Let me get right on that.

14:53.393 --> 14:54.758
Easy.

14:55.311 --> 14:58.144
He's just showing me how strong he is.

14:58.314 --> 14:59.474
Makes me proud.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.475
-Yeah.
-Hey, watch it.

15:04.320 --> 15:07.107
SAM: That's your damn father.
-I know exactly who he is.

15:07.281 --> 15:08.487
MELINDA:
Oh, it's nothing.

15:08.658 --> 15:10.990
It's a little game
they ought to play in private.

15:11.536 --> 15:14.152
He'll make it up to me. Won't you, boy?

15:14.330 --> 15:17.822
Maybe you need to talk
amongst yourselves, all right?

15:18.000 --> 15:21.993
Y'all listen to Sam.
He's always got the good ideas.

15:22.171 --> 15:23.672
No.

15:24.424 --> 15:25.584
It's all been said.

15:35.059 --> 15:39.769
-Hey, Sam. Sam.
-Hey. Look at you.

15:39.939 --> 15:43.773
-You doing what I think you're doing?
-Yup. Yes, sir.

15:43.943 --> 15:45.979
Me, Terry Bellefleur...

15:47.280 --> 15:48.941
...I'm moving in with Arlene Fowler.

15:49.699 --> 15:52.281
Congratulations.

15:52.452 --> 15:55.535
Ah! You're cracking my ribs, buddy.

15:57.248 --> 15:58.988
Hey, hey.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.294
Hey, now, it's gonna be okay.

16:03.171 --> 16:04.377
I mean, sure, it's scary.

16:05.465 --> 16:10.175
She's a little crazy, but so are--
ls everybody, you know?

16:10.344 --> 16:11.379
Don't worry.

16:12.263 --> 16:14.174
I ain't worried.

16:14.348 --> 16:16.555
I've never been so not worried.

16:17.477 --> 16:21.766
This is what normal people do, Sam.
They fall in love.

16:21.939 --> 16:25.056
They make each other laugh.
And they move in together.

16:25.234 --> 16:27.145
They raise kids. They fight over money.

16:27.320 --> 16:31.154
They get old and fat together,
and it's normal.

16:31.324 --> 16:32.905
And it's happening to me.

16:33.075 --> 16:34.736
[SNIFFLES]

16:34.911 --> 16:37.573
-I can't believe it.
-Well, I can.

16:37.747 --> 16:39.408
Nobody deserves it more.

16:42.251 --> 16:44.742
ARLENE:
Baby? I don't feel too good today, okay?

16:44.921 --> 16:48.254
I ain't cleaned nothing,
I ain't cleared nothing out.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.249
I'm the luckiest man in the world.

16:53.095 --> 16:54.756
Coming, honey.

16:55.264 --> 16:56.720
JOE LEE:
You be careful with that.

16:56.891 --> 17:00.930
Oh, no, no. We can't be kissing right
now. Just put that in the living room.

17:04.899 --> 17:06.389
Happy for you, Arlene.

17:07.735 --> 17:09.020
Thank you, Sam.

17:10.488 --> 17:14.197
Oh, God.
I never thought it would happen again.

17:14.367 --> 17:18.280
And again, and again. Ha, ha, ha.

17:18.454 --> 17:21.946
And that other time too.
But especially now.

17:23.793 --> 17:26.079
Oh, sweet Jesus, I am a hurting gator.

17:27.296 --> 17:28.456
Hey, you know, uh....

17:29.423 --> 17:30.458
Hey, Joe Lee.

17:32.343 --> 17:35.050
I got these tenants here.
You could be my on-site handyman.

17:35.930 --> 17:40.469
ARLENE:
Handyman? I got a list as long as my leg.

17:40.643 --> 17:43.806
-Well, if it don't hurt my back.
-He'd love to.

17:45.648 --> 17:46.808
Time for work, bro.

17:47.817 --> 17:50.650
Have a great day, Sam.

18:20.474 --> 18:22.851
ALCIDE: It's gone too far
and it's picking up speed.

18:23.019 --> 18:25.852
I gotta tell the packmaster everything.

18:26.022 --> 18:27.933
Gonna run errands. Won't take long.

18:28.107 --> 18:30.519
-What's a packmaster?
-Goddamn it.

18:30.693 --> 18:33.856
-I gotta do what I gotta do.
-This is Were business.

18:34.030 --> 18:36.021
It's against our laws to tell you anything.

18:36.198 --> 18:39.611
I've been listening to dark,
private thoughts since I was a little girl.

18:39.785 --> 18:42.697
-Keeping secrets is how I survive, Alcide.
-No.

18:42.872 --> 18:47.206
Then I'll have to dig it out of your head,
and I really don't like to do that.

18:50.338 --> 18:52.329
Pack isn't a democracy.

18:52.506 --> 18:54.792
Most Weres don't have much sense.
You saw.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.709
They're all teeth and fight and sex.

18:57.887 --> 18:59.047
Packmaster's our alpha.

18:59.221 --> 19:01.963
He makes the big decisions,
keeps the rest of us in line.

19:02.141 --> 19:04.883
How much does your packmaster know
about last night?

19:05.061 --> 19:07.894
That's what I have to find out.
He'll tell us what to do.

19:08.064 --> 19:10.851
-I'm coming along.
-I am not breaking more rules for you.

19:11.025 --> 19:13.687
Then you might as well invite
Debbie over to tear me up...

19:13.861 --> 19:16.227
...because that's what she's gonna
try to do.

19:16.572 --> 19:17.732
[SIGHS]

19:17.907 --> 19:19.147
Work with me, Alcide.

19:20.409 --> 19:21.660
It gets easier.

19:24.246 --> 19:25.577
[GROANS]

19:29.126 --> 19:32.994
-|'|| take the car accident on Euclid.
-|'|| take the vandalism at the high school.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.912
What do I do?

19:36.175 --> 19:38.336
File that for me, will you, babe?

20:19.510 --> 20:22.798
Stackhouse! You're driving me nuts.

20:22.972 --> 20:26.260
I can't work a desk no more, Andy.

20:26.976 --> 20:29.217
It's sucking the life out of me.

20:29.395 --> 20:32.728
I need a cold case.
I need a special assignment.

20:32.898 --> 20:35.480
I need some fucking thing to do
right fucking now...

20:35.651 --> 20:40.486
...or I'll blow up like a M80
and take this whole place with me.

20:40.656 --> 20:44.820
Don't worry.
I'll give you just what you need.

21:17.693 --> 21:20.025
[WOLF HOWLING]

21:20.821 --> 21:22.357
[BARKING]

21:30.873 --> 21:32.363
[GROWLING]

21:38.464 --> 21:40.580
[HOWLING]

21:46.472 --> 21:49.088
Suck on that thing. Don't play with it.

21:49.266 --> 21:50.881
There you go.

21:51.060 --> 21:55.269
Now, this here cigarillo
is called a Macanudo Ascot.

21:55.439 --> 22:00.058
